      "source": [
        "# Implementation of fastText, BERT, and the phoneme LSTM model\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "*   fastText: breaks words into smaller character n-grams, allowing it to handle rare, misspelled, and out-of-vocabulary words better than traditional models like Word2Vec.\n",
        "*   BERT: stands for Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers. It understands context by analyzing words in both directions\n",
        "* LSTM: is RNN designed to learn and remember long-term dependencies in sequential data, which is Japanese phonemes in this case.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "701d3a97"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Load Dataset\n",
        "\n",
        "### Dataset:\n",
        "Load the `data/onomatopoeia.csv` dataset. The dataset compose of 220 unique onomatopoeia words, categorized as Movement, Sound, Visual, Texture, and Emotion. Those definitions are following:\n",
        "\n",
        "*  Movement: Words describing physical motion or manner of movement\n",
        "*  Sound: Words directly imitating auditory phenomena\n",
        "* Visual: Words describing visual states or appearances\n",
        "* Texture: Words describing tactile sensations, surface qualities, or material properties.\n",
        "* Emotion: Words describing psychological states, feelings, or internal conditions.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "846e6556"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "CSV_FILE = \"data/onomatopoeia.csv\"\n",
        "\n",
        "colorMap = {\n",
        "    \"emotion\": \"royalblue\",\n",
        "    \"movement\": \"orange\",\n",
        "    \"sound\": \"forestgreen\",\n",
        "    \"texture\": \"crimson\",\n",
        "    \"visual\": \"mediumpurple\"\n",
        "}"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "xeqVBr3udsve"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Install necessary libraries"
